## Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the Meetlify frontend application.

### Changes Made

#### 1. Installed Dependencies
- Added `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 to project dependencies
- Used npm (the project's package manager) to install the package

#### 2. Modified Files
- **package.json**: Added `@vercel/analytics` to dependencies
- **package-lock.json**: Updated with new package and its dependencies (82 new packages)
- **src/App.jsx**: Added Analytics component integration

#### 3. Implementation Details

**In src/App.jsx:**
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react'`
- Wrapped the existing Routes component in a React Fragment (`<>...</>`)
- Added `<Analytics />` component after the Routes component to enable analytics tracking across all pages

This implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for React applications, ensuring the Analytics component is rendered on every page of the application.

### Technical Notes

- The Analytics component was added at the root level (in App.jsx) to track all routes in the application, including:
  - Public routes (landing page, events list, event details, registration)
  - Admin routes (dashboard, events management, registrations)
  
- The implementation is non-invasive and maintains the existing code structure
- No breaking changes were introduced
- Build and linter checks passed successfully

### Verification Performed

✅ Package installation completed successfully (npm install)
✅ Build compilation passed (npm run build)
✅ Linter check completed with no new errors (npm run lint)
✅ Lock file updated correctly (package-lock.json)

### Next Steps for Activation

To enable analytics tracking in production:
1. Deploy this code to Vercel
2. Go to the Vercel dashboard → Analytics section
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics data will begin collecting automatically after deployment

The implementation is complete and ready for deployment.
